40|$|In {{the context}} of the Anderson theory of high T_c cuprates, we develop a BCS theory for Luttinger liquids. If the Luttinger {{interaction}} is much stronger than the BCS potential we find that the BCS equation is quite modified compared to usual BCS equation for <b>Fermi</b> <b>liquids.</b> In particular T_c predicted by the BCS equation for Luttinger liquids is quite higher than the usual T_c for <b>Fermi</b> <b>liquids...</b>|$|R
