40|$|Nonrelativistic <b>Fermi</b> <b>liquids</b> in d+ 1 {{dimensions}} exhibit generalized Fermi surfaces: (d-p) -dimensional submanifolds in the momentum-frequency space supporting gapless excitations. We {{show that}} the universality classes of stable Fermi surfaces are classified by K-theory, with the pattern of stability determined by Bott periodicity. The Atiyah-Bott-Shapiro construction implies that the low-energy modes near a Fermi surface exhibit relativistic invariance in the transverse p+ 1 dimensions. This suggests an intriguing parallel between norelativistic <b>Fermi</b> <b>liquids</b> and D-branes of string theory. Comment: 4 pages, revte...|$|R
